2. Initialize the Mobile Environment
Open your terminal inside the root directory (my-lottery-app/) and execute the configuration installation:

Bash
# Initialize npm project structure
npm init -y

# Install Core Capacitor packages
npm install @capacitor/core @capacitor/cli

# Initialize your application configurations
npx cap init "MI Lottery Analytics" "com.milottery.analytics" --web-dir=www
3. Attach Target Mobile Platforms
Add the specific native platforms you plan to compile for:

Bash
# Install platform engines
npm install @capacitor/android @capacitor/ios

# Add platforms to your project build directory
npx cap add android
npx cap add ios
4. Sync and Build
Every time you make adjustments to your code inside the www/index.html file, run the sync command to push updates into your native Android/iOS IDE compilation environments:

Bash
npx cap sync
5. Open in Native Tooling
Launch the project inside Android Studio or Xcode to compile, run on simulated test devices, or generate production .apk or .ipa bundle binaries for App Store distribution:

Bash
npx cap open android
npx cap open ios
Necessary Mobile Optimization Adjustments
Before compiling, you should make a few minor layout adjustments to your index.html file to ensure a flawless mobile user experience:

Viewport Adjustments: Add viewport-fit=cover into your viewport meta tag to ensure your interface layout extends smoothly behind mobile camera notches and native bottom gesture bars:

HTML
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover">
Touch Optimization: Add user-select: none; and remove -webkit-app-region: drag; (which is only for Electron desktop window dragging environments) so that the app behaves correctly when scrolled or tapped on mobile screens.

Responsive Layouts: Change the grid patterns and side navigation setups to scale correctly on narrow mobile viewports. For example, change .layout to flex-direction: column; on mobile screens so the sidebar drops cleanly down to a bottom tab configuration or a collapsable menu drawer.
